==English==
===Etymology===
From medieval Latin ''[[acuatus]]'', past participle of ''[[acuare]]'', variant of ''[[acuere]]'' "to sharpen", from ''[[acus]]'' "needle".

===Adjective===
'''acuate'''
# [[sharpen|Sharpened]]; sharp-pointed.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|acuat|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To [[sharpen]]; to make [[pungent]]; to [[quicken]].

